title: The Ipcress File: Season 1
description: Joe Cole (Harry Palmer) begins his intelligence career in Berlin, while Jean Courtney (Lucy Boynton) get close to CIA agent Paul Maddox (Ashley Thomas) in this loose adaptation of Len Deighton's 1962 book with influences from the 1965 film with Michael Caine. [Premiered originally in the UK on ITV on 6 Mar 2022 and set to air in the US on AMC+ in 19 May 2022]

title: Ridley Road: Season 1
description: Vivien Epstein (Agnes O'Casey) moves to London in 1962 to find her ex-boyfriend Jack Morris (Tom Varey) and soon finds herself involved in spying on the National Socialist Movement in this four-part drama series based on the novel by Jo Bloom. [Premiered originally in the UK on BBC One on 3 Oct 2021 and in the US on PBS on 1 May 2022]

title: Shining Girls: Season 1
description: Kirby Mazrachi (Elisabeth Moss) teams with reporter Dan Velazquez (Wagner Moura) to identify her attacker after she learns a murder case resembles the assault she suffered years ago in this drama based on The Shining Girls novel by Lauren Beukes.

title: The Offer: Season 1
description: The limited series dramatizes producer Albert S. Ruddy's (Miles Teller) experience while making Francis Ford Coppola's "The Godfather."

title: We Own This City: Season 1
description: The limited series co-created by David Simon and George Pelecanos centers on members of the Baltimore Police Department's Gun Trace Task Force that robbed and extorted citizens for several years before a federal investigation uncovered their crimes in this adaptation of Justin Fenton's non-fiction book.

title: Billy the Kid: Season 1
description: The drama series written by Michael Hirst centers on of how William H. Bonney became the famous outlaw Billy the Kid (Tom Blyth).

title: Gaslit: Season 1
description: Martha Mitchell (Julia Roberts), the wife of Nixon's Attorney General (Sean Penn) and the Nixon administrations attempts to keep her from talking about Watergate are at the center of the limited series based on the first season of the Slate podcast Slow Burn.

title: The Baby: Season 1
description: 38-year-old Natasha (Michelle De Swarte) didn't want a child but finds herself saddled with a baby in this horror comedy limited series co-created by Siân Robins-Grace and Lucy Gaymer.

title: The Man Who Fell to Earth (2022): Season 1
description: An alien (Chiwetel Ejiofor) seeks Justin Falls (Naomie Harris), a scientist, who he believes can help save his species in this continuation inspired by the novel by Walter Tevis and the 1976 film of the same name with David Bowie.

title: They Call Me Magic: Season 1
description: The four-part Apple documentary series from Rick Famuyiwa looks at Earvin "Magic" Johnson's career from his days playing high school basketball to his current business ventures.

title: A Very British Scandal
description: The three-part miniseries written by Sarah Phelps, focuses on the 1963 divorce of the Duke and Duchess of Argyll (Paul Bettany and Claire Foy). [Premiered originally in the UK on BBC One on 26 Dec 2021; in the US on Prime Video on 22 Apr 2022]

title: Heartstopper: Season 1
description: Openly gay Charlie (Kit Connor) and rugby player Nick (Joe Locke) becomes friends at a British high school in this adaptation of Alice Oseman's graphic novel of the same name.

title: Captive Audience: Season 1
description: The three-part documentary series directed by Jessica Dimmock features interviews, archival footage, and clips from the NBC miniseries "I Know My First Name is Steven" as it looks at the media's role in the tragic story that began with Steven Stayner's 1972 kidnapping and years later, the arrest of his older brother, Cary, for killing four women in 1999.

title: Conversations with a Killer: The John Wayne Gacy Tapes
description: The three-part documentary from Joe Berlinger about serial killer John Wayne Gacy features interviews with survivors, officers, and attorneys as well as select audio from the 60 hours of tapes recorded by investigators while he was on death row.

title: Doctor Who: Legend of the Sea Devils
description: The second of three specials finds the Doctor, Yaz and Dan in 19th-century China where pirate Madame Ching (Crystal Yu) releases a Sea Devil while seeking a lost treasure.

title: The First Lady: Season 1
description: The anthology series created by Aaron Cooley focuses on the personal and political lives of Michelle Obama (Viola Davis), Betty Ford (Michelle Pfeiffer) and Eleanor Roosevelt (Gillian Anderson).

title: Swimming with Sharks: Season 1
description: Originally slated for Quibi, the series inspired by George Huang's 1994 comedy of the same name follows intern Lou Simms (Kiernan Shipka) as she becomes obsessed with her boss, Joyce Holt (Diane Kruger), studio head of Fountain Pictures.

title: Outer Range: Season 1
description: Wyoming rancher Royal Abbott (Josh Brolin) and his family are dealing with the disappearance of a family member, a rival family wanting to buy them out when something mysterious appears on their land in this Western sci-fi thriller created by Brian Watkins.

title: Anatomy of a Scandal: Season 1
description: The legal thriller anthology co-created by David Kelley with Melissa James Gibson is based on the Sarah Vaughan novel of the same name about the scandal that endangers the marriage of an ambitious minister (Rupert Friend) in parliament and the barrister (Michelle Dockery) who prosecutes the case.

title: Roar (2022): Season 1
description: The anthology series about how women deal with the world today from Carly Mensch and Liz Flahive is based on the book of short stories by Cecilia Ahern.

title: The Garcias: Season 1
description: The reboot of Nickelodeon's "The Brothers Garcia" follows the San Antonio, Texas-based family as they get together at a beach vacation house in Mexico.

title: Killing It: Season 1
description: After failing to secure a loan for his business idea, Craig (Craig Robinson) learns of the money available for hunting snakes from his Australian Uber driver (Claudia O'Doherty) in this comedy series from Dan Goor and Luke Del Tredici.

title: Not So Pretty: Season 1
description: Narrated by Keke Palmer, the four-part documentary from Kirby Dick and Amy Ziering explores the possible dangers contained in cosmetics and personal care products.

title: The Kardashians: Season 1
description: Kris, Kourtney, Kim, Khloé, Kendall and Kylie are back in this Hulu reality series.

title: Our Great National Parks: Season 1
description: Narrated by President Barack Obama, the five-part documentary series from the executive producer of Blue Planet II explores a variety of national parks on five continents.

title: Hard Cell: Season 1
description: The prison mockumentary created and written by Catherine Tate is set in the fictional female prison, HMP Woldsley, where the inmates (at least three played by Tate) rehearse a musical directed by ex-EastEnders star Cheryl Fergison.

title: Why Didn't They Ask Evans?
description: Bobby Jones (Will Poulter) and his friend, Lady Frances "Frankie" Derwent (Lucy Boynton) find a dying man while playing golf in this three-part adaptation of Agatha Christie's book of the same name from Hugh Laurie (who also had a minor part and directed).

title: 61st Street: Season 1
description: Public Defender Franklin Roberts (Courtney B. Vance) takes up the case of Moses Johnson (Tosin Cole), a Chicago high school track star accused of being involved the death of an officer during a drug bust in his neighborhood. [Also airs on ALLBLK]

title: Tokyo Vice: Season 1
description: Set in the 1990s, reporter Jake Adelstein (Ansel Elgort) covers the Tokyo Metropolitan Police beat for a Japanese newspaper in this crime drama series loosely inspired Jake Adelstein's memoir.

title: The Ultimatum: Marry or Move On (2022): Season 1
description: Six couples exam their readiness for marriage by living with a different person for 3 weeks before deciding to go down the aisle or to move on in this reality series hosted by Nick and Vanessa Lachey.

title: Jimmy Savile: A British Horror Story: Season 1
description: The two-part documentary from Rowan Deacon looks at how Top of the Pops/Jim'll Fix It host Jimmy Savile used his position to sexually abuse children and adults for decades.

title: The Invisible Pilot: Season 1
description: The three-part documentary series directed by Phil Lott and Ari Mark looks into the story of an Arkansas pilot named Gary Betzner, who was thought dead by his family but had instead became involved in drug/weapons smuggling for the Contras.

title: Benjamin Franklin: Season 1
description: The life of Benjamin Franklin, one of the founding fathers of the US, is explored in the two-part documentary written by Dayton Duncan and directed by Ken Burns.

title: The Outlaws: Season 1
description: Seven people serving their community service sentence discover a bag of cash in this British comedy thriller co-created by Stephen Merchant and Elgin James.

title: Jerrod Carmichael: Rothaniel
description: The third stand-up special for Jerrod Carmichael was recorded at New York City's Blue Note Jazz Club.

title: Slow Horses: Season 1
description: A group of MI5 agents demoted to desk duty led by Jackson Lamb (Gary Oldman) seek redemption in the espionage drama based on Mick Herron's Slough House novels.

title: How We Roll: Season 1
description: After being laid off, Tom (Pete Holmes) aims to become a professional bowler with encouragement from his mentor (Chi McBride), his wife (Katie Lowes), son (Mason Wells), and mother (Julie White) in this comedy based on professional bowler Tom Smallwood's life, from writer Mark Gross.

title: Julia (2022): Season 1
description: The comedy series from Daniel Goldfarb is based on the life of Julia Child (Sarah Lancashire) and her TV show, The French Chef.

title: Moon Knight: Season 1
description: Steven Grant (Oscar Isaac) is hearing voices and having vivid dreams that he soon discovers is related to sharing a body with a mercenary named Marc Spector in this series created by Jeremy Slater and based on the Marvel character.

title: The Girl From Plainville: Season 1
description: The limited series based on an Esquire article by Jesse Barron focuses on Michelle Carter's (Elle Fanning) relationship with Conrad Roy III (Colton Ryan), his death and her conviction of involuntary manslaughter.

title: Lizzo's Watch Out for the Big Grrrls: Season 1
description: 10 women compete for a chance to join Lizzo on tour as one of her Big Grrrls in this competition reality series.

title: Pachinko: Season 1
description: The drama series based on the novel of the same name by Min Jin Lee follows four generations of a Korean family that moves to Japan and deal with war, love and making a living.

title: One Perfect Shot: Season 1
description: Created by Ava DuVernay and inspired by a Twitter account of the same name, filmmakers such as Jon M. Chu, Malcolm D. Lee, Kasi Lemmons, Patty Jenkins, Michael Mann, and Aaron Sorkin discuss how their iconic shots were done.

title: Halo: Season 1
description: Dr. Catherine Elizabeth Halsey (Natascha McElhone) and Master Chief Petty Officer John-117 (Pablo Schreiber) are introduced in the long-gestating sci-fi series based on the Xbox video game franchise set in 26th-century.

title: An Audience with Adele
description: Adele performs songs from her album "30", as well as some of her previous hits at the London Palladium in this special recorded on 6 November 2021. [Aired originally in the UK on ITV on 21 Nov 2021; in the US on NBC on 20 Mar 2022]

title: Before We Die: Season 1
description: Detective Inspector Hannah Laing (Lesley Sharp) seeks to find the killer of her colleague/lover with the help of his informant in this British adaptation of a Swedish series of the same name. [Aired originally in the UK on Channel 4 on 26 May 2021; in the US on PBS on 20 Mar 2022]

title: WeCrashed: Season 1
description: The relationship between WeWork founder Adam Neumann (Jared Leto) and his wife, Rebekah (Anne Hathaway), is at the center of the story of the rise and fall of shared workspace company in this limited series from Lee Eisenberg and Drew Crevello.

title: Is It Cake?: Season 1
description: On each episode, a panel of celebrity judges will guess which object is really cake and if they fail to select the baked good, the winning baker wins $10,000. The final three bakers compete for a $50,000 grand prize in this competitive reality series hosted by Mikey Day.

title: The Newsreader: Season 1
description: Set in 1986 Australia, star newsreader Helen Norville (Anna Torv) is paired up with reporter Dale Jennings (Sam Reid) to cover national and world news including the Challenger explosion, Halley’s Comet, the Russell Street bombing in Melbourne, and the AIDS crisis. [Aired originally in Australia on ABC TV on 15 Aug 2021; in the US on The Roku Channel on 18 Mar 2022]

title: Life & Beth: Season 1
description: An incident causes 30-something wine distributor Beth (Amy Schumer) to look back into her past and reassess who she is in this comedy series written, directed and produced by Schumer.

title: Human Resources: Season 1
description: The "Big Mouth" spinoff series looks at the lives of Hormone Monsters, Depression Kitties, Shame Wizards and the other creatures that guide humans through their own lives.

title: Welcome to Flatch: Season 1
description: Cousins Kelly Mallet (Chelsea Holmes) and Lloyd "Shrub" Mallett (Sam Straley) are some of the residents of a midwestern town being filmed by a documentry crew in this comedy series from Jenny Bicks and Paul Feig that was based on British mockumentary This Country. [The first seven episodes will be available on Hulu on 17 Mar 2022]

title: Minx: Season 1
description: In 1970s Los Angeles, a young feminist named Joyce (Ophelia Lovibond) works with a low-rent publisher (Jake Johnson) to start the first erotic magazine for women in this comedy series written by Ellen Rapoport.

title: DMZ: Season 1
description: Alma (Rosario Dawson) searches for son in the near future where a second civil war has caused Manhattan to become a demilitarized zone in The limited series based on the comic series of the same name and executive produced by Ava DuVernay and Roberto Patino.

title: Bad Vegan: Fame. Fraud. Fugitives.: Season 1
description: The four-part documentary from Chris Smith looks into how "Vegan Queen" Sarma Melngailis, became known as the "Vegan Fugitive" after meeting a man named Shane Fox in 2011.

title: Servant of the People: Season 1
description: A high-school teacher (played by Volodymyr Zelensky before he became Ukraine's president) ends up as president after his diatribe about corruption is uploaded online in this satirical political comedy. [Aired originally in Ukraine from 2015-2019 and in the US on Netflix from 2017-2021, before returning on 16 Mar 2022]

title: Phoenix Rising
description: The two-part documentary produced and directed by Amy Berg centers on Evan Rachel Wood as she talks about her experience with domestic violence and advocates for The Phoenix Act, which extended the statute of limitations in California for domestic violence felonies from three years to five years.

title: The Last Days of Ptolemy Grey: Season 1
description: Suffering from dementia, Ptolemy (Samuel L. Jackson) gets a new teenaged caretaker (Dominique Fishback) and together, they discover treatment that temporarily restores Ptolemy's memories in the limited series based on the novel of the same name by Walter Mosley.

title: Bust Down: Season 1
description: The comedy from Lorne Michaels follows the antics of four casino employees (Jak Knight, Langston Kerman, Sam Jay and Chris Redd).

title: That Dirty Black Bag: Season 1
description: The spaghetti western drama centers on the eight-day conflict between sheriff Arthur McCoy (Dominic Cooper) and bounty hunter Red Bill (Douglas Booth).

title: The Andy Warhol Diaries: Season 1
description: The six-part documentary series from Ryan Murphy and director Andrew Rossi looks at Andy Warhol's life based on the artist's posthumously published diaries.

title: The Thing About Pam: Season 1
description: The 2011 murder of Betsy Faria (Katy Mixon) was originally pinned on her husband (Glenn Fleshler) but a retrial soon revealed her co-worker Pam Hupp's (Renée Zellweger) involvement in this limited series based on the real-life case.

title: Shining Vale: Season 1
description: Pat and Terry Phelps (Courteney Cox and Greg Kinnear) move their family from a small Brooklyn apartment into a Victorian mansion with a terrible history in Shining Vale, Connecticut in this horror comedy series created by Jeff Astrof and Sharon Horgan.

title: The Courtship: Season 1
description: The dating reality completive series hosted by Rick Edwards features 16 men seek win the heart of Nicole Remy and the approval of her court (i.e. family) the old-fashioned way with letter writing, archery, fencing, and attending balls at a British 19th century castle.

title: Winning Time: The Rise of the Lakers Dynasty: Season 1
description: The Adam McKay drama series centers on the Los Angeles Lakers during the 1980s when they won five NBA championships.

title: Pieces of Her: Season 1
description: After 30-year-old Andy Oliver (Bella Heathcote) and her mother Laura (Toni Collette) are involved in a violent incident in their small Georgia town, Andy searches for answers in this adaptation of Karin Slaughter's book of the same name.

title: The Boys Presents: Diabolical: Season 1
description: The animated anthology spinoff of The Boys features short (less than 15 minutes) stories written by Awkwafina, Garth Ennis, Ilana Glazer, Evan Goldberg, Seth Rogen, Justin Roiland, Andy Samberg, and Aisha Tyler.

title: The Dropout: Season 1
description: The eight-part series based on the podcast from ABC News' Rebecca Jarvis tells the story of the rise and fall of Theranos and its CEO Elizabeth Holmes (Amanda Seyfried).

title: Joe vs Carole: Season 1
description: The limited series based on the Wondery podcast "Joe Exotic" focuses on Carole Baskin (Kate McKinnon) and how her rivalry with Joe "Exotic" Schreibvogel (John Cameron Mitchell) grew.

title: The Tourist: Season 1
description: A British man (Jamie Dornan) tries to figure out why someone tried to drive him off the road in the Australian outback in the thriller series from Harry and Jack Williams. [Premiered originally in the UK on BBC One on 1 Jan 2022; in Australia on Stan on 2 Jan 2022 and in the US on HBO Max on 3 Mar 2022]

title: Our Flag Means Death: Season 1
description: The comedy series from David Jenkins and Taika Waititi is loosely based on the true story Stede Bonnet (Rhys Darby), an 18th-century wealthy landowner who gave it all up to to become a pirate.

title: Gaming Wall Street: Season 1
description: The two-part documentary narrated by Kieran Culkin looks at the story behind Reddit, GameStop stock and Robinhood in January 2021.

title: The Guardians of Justice: Season 1
description: After the death of Marvelous Man, The Guardians of Justice must regroup as humanity descends into chaos in the superheroes series from Adi Shankar.

title: Super Pumped: The Battle for Uber: Season 1
description: The anthology series based on Mike Isaac's book of the same name will focus on Uber and its CEO, Travis Kalanick (Joseph Gordon-Levitt).

title: Vikings: Valhalla: Season 1
description: The Vikings sequel picks up more than a 100 years after the end of the History series and features Leif Erikson (Sam Corlett), Freydis Eriksdotter (Frida Gustavsson), Harald Harada (Leo Suter) and King William the Conqueror.

title: Frederick Douglass: In Five Speeches
description: Nicole Beharie, Colman Domingo, Jonathan Majors, Denzel Whitaker and Jeffrey Wright perform five of Frederick Douglass’ speeches in the special about the life of the 19th century activist inspired by David Blight’s biography, "Frederick Douglass: Prophet of Freedom."

title: Cat Burglar
description: Rowdy the Cat looks to steal art from a museum guarded by Peanut the Security Dog in the Charlie Brooker animated interactive special that was inspired by Tex Avery cartoons.

title: Race: Bubba Wallace: Season 1
description: The documentary series focuses on NASCAR driver Bubba Wallace, his decision to speak out in 2020 about social justice issues and driving for Michael Jordan's 23XI Racing in 2021.

title: The Endgame: Season 1
description: There's a mysterious reason behind a group of coordinated bank heists in New York City planned by Elena Federova (Morena Baccarin) and FBI agent Val Fitzgerald (Ryan Michelle Bathé) is out to stop it in this thriller written by Nicholas Wootton.

title: All American: Homecoming: Season 1
description: Set at the fictional HBCU Bringston University, Simone (Geffri Maya), a tennis prospect from Beverly Hills and Damon (Peyton Alex Smith), a baseball recruit from Chicago juggle school, sports, and relationships in this spin-off of All American.

title: Abraham Lincoln
description: The seven-and-a-half-hour miniseries on President Lincoln life airing over three consecutive nights is based on Doris Kearns Goodwin's book "Leadership: In Turbulent Times."

title: From: Season 1
description: The sci-fi horror series created by John Griffin centers on a town where everyone who ends up there is trapped and while trying to find a way out, they also must try to avoid creatures that come out at night from the surrounding forests.

title: The Cuphead Show!: Season 1
description: The animated comedy series based on the Cuphead video game follows the adventures of Cuphead and his brother Mugman.

title: Severance: Season 1
description: Mark Scout (Adam Scott) is one of several employees at Lumon Corporation who undergo a procedure which separates their work and home memories so they can only recall the ones related to where they are in this sci-fi thriller from Ben Stiller and created by Dan Erickson.

title: Lincoln's Dilemma: Season 1
description: The four-part documentary series narrated by Jeffrey Wright looks at the life of President Lincoln and his decision to end slavery.

title: jeen-yuhs: A Kanye Trilogy: Season 1
description: The three-part documentary from Clarence "Coodie" Simmons and Chike Ozah about the life and career of rapper Kanye West features footage shot over 20+ years.

title: Ali Wong: Don Wong
description: The third Netflix stand-up special for Ali Wong was directed by Nahnatchka Khan at New Jersey's The Count Basie Theater in November 2021.

title: Bel-Air: Season 1
description: The dramatic reboot of NBC's 1990s sitcom "The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air" follows Will (Jabari Banks) as he moves from West Philadelphia to the Bel-Air mansion of his uncle and aunt (Adrian Holmes and Cassandra Freeman).

title: everything's gonna be all white : Season 1
description: The three-part documentry series directed by Sacha Jenkins looks at the history of racism.

title: Inventing Anna: Season 1
description: Vivian (Anna Chlumsky), a journalist investigates purported German heiress Anna Delvey (Julia Garner), who may be a con woman in this limited series from Shonda Rhimes inspired by the New York Magazine article by Jessica Pressler.

title: The Girl Before
description: Jane (Gugu Mbatha-Raw) moves into a house designed by architect (David Oyelowo), but there are very specific rules she must follow in this adaptation of JP Delaney’s novel of the same name. [Premiered originally in the UK on BBC One on 19 Dec 2021 and in the US on HBO Max on 10 Feb 2022]

title: Ms. Pat: Y'all Wanna Hear Something Crazy?
description: The solo stand-up special for Ms. Pat was directed by Robert Townsend at the Atlanta Comedy Theater.

title: Angela Black: Season 1
description: Angela Black (Joanne Froggatt) seeks to discover what her husband (Michiel Huisman) has planned after a private investigator (Samuel Adewunmi) approaches her with shocking information in this thriller series. [Premiered in the UK on ITV on 10 Oct 2021 and in the US on Spectrum on 7 Feb 2022]

title: Power Book IV: Force: Season 1
description: Tommy Egan (Joseph Sikora) ends up in Chicago and becoming involved in the drug trade in this latest Power spinoff.

title: Phat Tuesdays: Season 1
description: The history and influence of Guy Torry's all-black comedy night at The Comedy Store is discussed by such guests as Anthony Anderson, Tichina Arnold, Nick Cannon, Dave Chappelle, Snoop Dogg, Cedric the Entertainer, Tiffany Haddish, Steve Harvey, Lil Rel Howery, Regina King, Jo Koy, Luenell, Flame Monroe, Jay Pharoah, Craig Robinson, JB Smoove, Chris Tucker, and Kym Whitley.

title: Reacher: Season 1
description: Based on Lee Child's first Reacher novel, retired Military Police Officer Jack Reacher (Alan Ritchson) is arrested for murder just as he arrives at the small Georgia town of Margrave in this drama series from Nick Santora.

title: Suspicion (2022): Season 1
description: When the 21-year-old son of a well-known American businesswoman (Uma Thurman) is kidnapped from his New York hotel, four British citizens staying at the same hotel become suspects in this adaptation of the Israeli drama False Flag.

title: Murderville: Season 1
description: In this adaptation of the British series, Murder in Successville, each episode features Homicide Detective Terry Seattle (Will Arnett) with a new murder case and a new guest star as his partner. With no script, Kumail Nanjiani, Conan O'Brien, Annie Murphy, Sharon Stone, Ken Jeong, and Marshawn Lynch must improvise and try to figure out the killer.

title: Pam & Tommy: Season 1
description: The marriage between Pamela Anderson (Lily James) and Tommy Lee (Sebastian Stan) and how their sex tape became public is at the center of this limited series from Seth Rogen and Evan Goldberg.

title: The Real Dirty Dancing: Season 1
description: Brie Bella, Corbin Bleu, Tyler Cameron, Cat Cora, Howie Dorough, Antonio Gates, Anjelah Johnson-Reyes and Loni Love team up in pairs to learn the dance moves in Dirty Dancing and seek to be named the best "Baby" and "Johnny" in this celebrity competitive dance series hosted by Stephen "tWitch" Boss.
